    "original_title": "Queens: Metropolitan Avenue - Forest Avenue",
    "text": "Metropolitan Avenue, east from Forest Avenue, showing at the corner H. Ruege\u2019s store.  The house in which the store is located was erected about 1840 and the store was opened in 1852 or 53.   Adjoining it on the left is Herman Ring\u2019s Real Estate Office.  The next building is the Volunteer Fireman\u2019s Engine House now the Metropolitan Democratic Club.  The building at the right is 6225 Forest Avenue.  This is a set of two views.\nApril 1925\nView 2:\t1922\nEugene L. Armbruster Collection\n",
